capacityMIB.name: capacityMIB

revisions.description: Update contact information, Change object name chassis to chassisCap due to collsion with chassis in ctron-mib-names.txt. SSR enterprise mibs apply to the Riverstone RS product line and Enterasys SSR.

capacityMIB.contactinfo: Enterasys Networks 35 Industrial Way, P.O. Box 5005 Rochester, NH 03867-0505 (603) 332-9400 support@enterasys.com http://www.enterasys.com
capacityMIB.description: This module defines a schema to access RS system resource capacity statistics.

SSRMemoryType.name: SSRMemoryType
SSRMemoryType.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each non-volatile memory device supported by the SSR series of products.

SSRCapabilityType.name: SSRCapabilityType
SSRCapabilityType.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for the different capabilities of the SSR chassis.

SSRStatusType.name: SSRStatusType
SSRStatusType.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each possible state a task on the SSR can be in.

capChassisSlotCount.name: capChassisSlotCount
capChassisSlotCount.description: The maximum number of slots in the chassis, including the slot for the CPU module.

capChassisSlotsUsed.name: capChassisSlotsUsed
capChassisSlotsUsed.description: The number of slots used in the chassis. This number includes the slot used for the CPU module, if any.

capChassisSlotsFree.name: capChassisSlotsFree
capChassisSlotsFree.description: The number of free slots in the chassis. This includes all of the available slots not used by the CPU or redundant CPU card.

capChassisCPURedundancy.name: capChassisCPURedundancy
capChassisCPURedundancy.description: The chassis CPU redundancy capability of the SSR. This will be one of the following values: noSupport(1) -- feature not supported available(2) -- feature not in use enabled(3) -- feature in use and enabled disabled(4) -- feature in use and disabled

capChassisPSRedundancy.name: capChassisPSRedundancy
capChassisPSRedundancy.description: The chassis Power Supply redundancy capability of the SSR. This will be one of the following values: noSupport(1) -- feature not supported available(2) -- feature not in use enabled(3) -- feature in use and enabled disabled(4) -- feature in use and disabled

capChassisSFRedundancy.name: capChassisSFRedundancy
capChassisSFRedundancy.description: The chassis Switching Fabric redundancy capability of the SSR. This will be one of the following values: noSupport(1) -- feature not supported available(2) -- feature not in use enabled(3) -- feature in use and enabled disabled(4) -- feature in use and disabled

capCPUTable.name: capCPUTable
capCPUTable.description: Summary of CPU statistics. It is assumed that there is only one CPU per line card.

capCPUEntry.name: capCPUEntry
capCPUEntry.description: An entry containing CPU statistics information.

capCPUModuleIndex.name: capCPUModuleIndex
capCPUModuleIndex.description: The Slot index in which the current CPU is residing.

capCPUCurrentUtilization.name: capCPUCurrentUtilization
capCPUCurrentUtilization.description: The CPU utilization expressed as an integer percentage. This is calculated over the last 5 seconds at a 0.1 second interval as a simple average.

capCPUL3Learned.name: capCPUL3Learned
capCPUL3Learned.description: The total number of new layer 3 flows the CPU has processed and programmed into the Layer 3 hardware flow tables. Layer 3 flows are packets for IP or IPX protocols that will be routed from one subnet to another. Bridged flows or IP and IPX flows that originate and terminate in the same subnet are accounted for by capCPUL2Learned object.

capCPUL3Aged.name: capCPUL3Aged
capCPUL3Aged.description: The total number of Layer 3flows that have been removed from the layer 3 hardware flow tables across all modules by the Layer 3 aging task. This number may increase quickly if routing protocols are not stable. Removal or insertion of routes into the forwarding table will cause premature aging of flows. Flows are normally aged/removed from the hardware when there are no more packets being sent for a defined time period. This counter is cumulative from the time the system started.

capCPUL2Learned.name: capCPUL2Learned
capCPUL2Learned.description: The number of L2 flows or addresses learned. The intended result here is to see how many stations attempt to establish switched communication through the SSR.

capCPUL2Aged.name: capCPUL2Aged
capCPUL2Aged.description: The total number of L2 addresses or flows aged out. Hosts that end switched communication through the SSR are aged out every 15 seconds.

capCPUNIAReceived.name: capCPUNIAReceived
capCPUNIAReceived.description: The total number of packets received by the NIA chip. This is useful in gauging how many packets are forwarded to the CPU for processing.

capCPUNIATransmitted.name: capCPUNIATransmitted
capCPUNIATransmitted.description: The total number of packets transmitted by the NIA chip. This is useful in seeing how much the CPU is communicating directory with management stations and other routers.

capCPUMinThreshold.name: capCPUMinThreshold
capCPUMinThreshold.description: The CPU utilization expressed as an integer percentage. This value represents the threshold minimum value for capCPUCurrentUtilization that is used to reset the threshold testing for generation of the envCPUThresholdTrap. This value is equal to 0 by default. When this value or the value of capCPUMaxThreshold is equal to 0, no envCPUThresholdTrap will be generated.

capCPUMaxThreshold.name: capCPUMaxThreshold
capCPUMaxThreshold.description: The CPU utilization expressed as an integer percentage. This value represents the threshold maximum for capCPUCurrentUtilization which causes generation of the envCPUThresholdTrap. Another trap is not generated until the capCPUCurrentUtilization value has dropped below capCPUMinThreshold. When this value or the value of capCPUMinThreshold is equal to 0, no envCPUThresholdTrap will be generated.

capTaskTable.name: capTaskTable
capTaskTable.description: A summary of the tasks running on a CPU enabled module in the chassis.

capTaskEntry.name: capTaskEntry
capTaskEntry.description: An entry containing information on a task running on a CPU enabled module in the chassis including the memory consumption and current status.

capTaskModuleIndex.name: capTaskModuleIndex
capTaskModuleIndex.description: The module index on which the task is running.

capTaskIndex.name: capTaskIndex
capTaskIndex.description: A unique index assigned to a task instance. This index is unique to the task for the time SSR is booted. If the task is terminated, the index will not be reused for another task that might become active in the system.

capTaskName.name: capTaskName
capTaskName.description: The encrypted name assigned to this task. This is unique for each different type of task, but there may be multiple instances of the same task running in the system.

capTaskShed.name: capTaskShed
capTaskShed.description: The number of times this task has been scheduled to run. This is a cumulative count from the time the SSR was started.

capTaskStatus.name: capTaskStatus
capTaskStatus.description: The current status of this task.

capTaskUsed.name: capTaskUsed
capTaskUsed.description: The size of the memory consumed by this task. This can be used to monitor any excess memory use by a particular task and is expressed in bytes.

capMemoryTable.name: capMemoryTable
capMemoryTable.description: A summary of the non-volatile storage devices in the SSR.

capMemoryEntry.name: capMemoryEntry
capMemoryEntry.description: An entry containing information on a non-volatile memory device in the SSR.

capMemoryType.name: capMemoryType
capMemoryType.description: A type of storage device from the enumerated memory types.

capMemoryIndex.name: capMemoryIndex
capMemoryIndex.description: An index or enumeration for the entries of a particular memory type. This index corresponds to: -- Interface index for L2Hardware Type -- Module index for L3Hardware Type -- Enumeration for everything else.

capMemoryDescr.name: capMemoryDescr
capMemoryDescr.description: The description of the memory device.

capMemorySize.name: capMemorySize
capMemorySize.description: Memory device total memory capacity expressed in blocks.

capMemoryFree.name: capMemoryFree
capMemoryFree.description: Memory device free memory in blocks. This will include any unused memory between used memory blocks and is calculated by subtracting the memory used from the size of the memory device.

capMemoryUsed.name: capMemoryUsed
capMemoryUsed.description: Size of used memory on the memory device. This includes the blocks of memory that are only partially used and is expressed in blocks.

capMemoryBlockSize.name: capMemoryBlockSize
capMemoryBlockSize.description: Size of the memory blocks on the memory device. This is the minimum block size of memory returned when memory is requested and is expressed in bytes.

capMemoryFailures.name: capMemoryFailures
capMemoryFailures.description: The number of times a memory allocation in this memory device has failed. In the case of L2Hardware and L3Hardware types it expresses the number of times a Full Hash Bucket condition has been met.

capMemoryRemovable.name: capMemoryRemovable
capMemoryRemovable.description: Indicates if the memory type is removable.

capComplianceV10.name: capComplianceV10
capComplianceV10.description: The compliance statement for the SSR-CAPACITY-MIB.

capComplianceV20.name: capComplianceV20
capComplianceV20.description: The compliance statement for the SSR-CAPACITY-MIB.

capConfGroupV10.name: capConfGroupV10
capConfGroupV10.description: A set of managed objects that make up version 1.0 of the SSR capacity mib.

capConfGroupV20.name: capConfGroupV20
capConfGroupV20.description: A set of managed objects that make up version 2.0 of the SSR capacity mib.
